The paper deals with semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep convolutional neural networks for semantic segmentation is a common approach, and the paper proposes a new method for reducing the complexity of upsampling calculation. This involves constructing hypercolumns using feature maps obtained by a pyramid module and convolution layers of the base network, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of statistical process control (SPC) for controlling the learning rate after sampling, which is a technique used in quality control and process improvement (cs.CL).
